Your hips don’t lie. Have you ever gone to a yoga or dance class and unexpectedly get hit with a wave of emotions, tears, and a general release? The deep muscles of our hips are closely connected to the adrenal glands, which are responsible for processing our fight-or-flight emotions. They’re also our biggest stabilizing muscles and can often tense up and become tight in moments of emotional activation or triggers. This is one of the beautiful wonders of our mind-body wisdom. Hip openers can feel challenging at first, but stick with it, breathe, and let your body release ❤️🦋 

#dancetoheal #melodydancefit #hipmobility #hipopener #hips #movement

Did you know that frequent dancing of any kind is linked to a 76% lower risk of dementia? Dance triggers new connections in the brain and increases your cognitive & spacial memory. The benefits of dance go FAR beyond the physical. It can literally change the function of your brain. The older I get, the more dances I want to learn & remember. And till the day I die I will be preaching this message to the world: DANCE IS HEALING (even if you think you suck at it) Learn more about my 6 week online  @_dance_to_heal program to shift your energy, brain, and spirit. Everything I do, I do for this little girl. The little Persian girl who felt confused about her cultural identity and didn’t know where she belonged. The little girl who was shy, ashamed, and sick of being different. The girl who was bullied in school for being middle eastern, especially after 9/11. The little girl who had to navigate uncomfortable and racist questions from her friend’s parents about where she comes from. The little girl who felt so alone and insecure…until she put on her favorite songs and danced. When she danced she felt connected her power and all of her sorrows melted away. She danced and played in her room for hours, healing herself without realizing it. I wouldn’t be where I am today without her guiding me and reminding me. She is the reason I’ve dedicated my career to helping people celebrate every part of themselves, even the parts we are ashamed of. She is the reason I teach people to play, release, and heal themselves through dance. She is my muse and the brains behind my success. SO grateful and honored to be named a finalist for @austinunder40 and congrats to all the other finalists! #austin #melodydancefit @_dance_to_heal

I have so many emotions watching this video. At first glance, you might just think it’s another dance video (maybe even one of mine). But if you look closer, you’ll see that this is a revolutionary moment: A group of Iranian girls from the neighborhood of Ekbatan in Tehran are dancing to this viral challenge outside.  In Iran, they could be arrested or killed for dancing in public and showing their hair. They are risking their lives to experience the simple joy of dancing with their friends in public. They are my heroes and I wish I could dance with them ❤️@iraniandiasporacollective @persian #womenlifefreedom #freeiran #melodydancefit #dancechallenge #persian #internationalwomensday

People think dancing equates to upbeat happiness but it’s also about finding the sorrow in movement & music. This song elicits a somberness and makes me think of the masks we often wear around others to be more socially acceptable. We tend to mask our darkness, our uncertainties, our insecurities…even though we all have them. No human is above feeling alone & misunderstood at times. SO excited to open up our Dance To Heal program for the spring. This is a self-paced online program that integrates the science of psychology with the ritual of dance to unlock a deep connection. It’s about processing, releasing, and coming home to yourself with ease. ⁣
⁣
The wellness industry will always be hyping up the next bio hacking, optimizing, faster, stronger way to health. But I’m not here to do that. I’m not here to stress you or your body into going harder.⁣
⁣
I am here to remind you to slow down and go within. I’m here to help you activate your nervous system and take you back to your primal roots. I’m here to teach you concrete ways to add more play & presence to your life. ⁣
⁣
And most importantly, I’m here to tell you that dancing regularly will shift the energy of your entire life. ⁣
⁣
I’ve seen it happen over and over again. People start dancing weekly, rediscover their own power, and even carry themselves in a different demeanor. This powerful shift will then manifest in other areas of life that feel completely unrelated to your dancing, but it’s not. ⁣
⁣
It’s all connected and it’s all in the energetic body. ⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
#dancetoheal #somatictherapy #somatic #therapy #melodydancefit #dance #healing

After my events, people often share with me that they experienced an emotional release they weren’t expecting. One woman said “I started crying, then I started laughing bc I couldn’t believe I was crying during a Lil Jon song” ⁣🤣
⁣
Our emotions can sometimes be disguised as tension or stiffness in the body. How we mentally feel affects how we feel physically, and vice versa. When we repress emotions over time, it can lead to fatigue, restlessness, and a general misalignment. ⁣
⁣
While there are several modalities to somatically (through the body) release & calm your nervous system, my FAVORITE is dancing. ⁣
⁣
⁣
Whether it’s shaking, jumping, stomping, clapping—when we intentionally move, we create a sense of safety in our bodies that we may not have experienced before. These movements release stored energy while helping the brain recognize the difference between tension & relaxation. ⁣
⁣
So why do I like dancing the most? Because it’s efficient, powerful, and playful. It only takes a few minutes! Listen to one of your favorite songs, jump up and down, and shake out your hands. In just two minutes, you’ll activate your nervous system, feel more playful, and loosen up your body! #melodydancefit #dancetoheal

THE CRITIC VS THE CHEERLEADER: The critic inside told me not to post this video. They said it’s not your best—it’s sloppy and not good enough. ⁣
⁣
But the cheerleader inside reminded me how far I’ve come and how scared I use to be of taking an intermediate class at @theplaygroundla ⁣
⁣
I believe we all have both a critic and a cheerleader inside. The critic will try to convince you it’s better not be seen at all than to be seen as imperfect. But the cheerleader sees things differently. The cheerleader reminds you to be PROUD of your milestones, whether it looks messy or not. The cheerleader sees power in being seen as you are and wants you to celebrate the present moment. ⁣
⁣
⁣
So today, I turned down my critic and listened to my cheerleader. I’m no longer letting my critic call the shots. I hope this inspires you to do the same 💜

“A young woman walks down a street in Tehran, her hair uncovered, her jeans ripped, midriff exposed to the hot Iranian sun. An unmarried couple walk hand in hand. A woman holds her head high when asked by Iran’s once-feared police to put a hijab on, and tells them: “Screw you!” - BBC News ⁣
⁣
These acts of rebellion would have been unthinkable to Iranians this time last year. But that was before the death in the police’s custody of 22-year-old Mahsa Amini, who had been accused of not wearing her hijab properly. This sparked the biggest anti government revolution in Iran since 1979. As an Iranian American, it pains me to see how much of a violent fight it is for women to simply have autonomy in their everyday lives. Even DANCING publicly in Iran is illegal. ⁣
⁣
So today, on national dance day, I honor Mahsa Amini and all of the brave people in Iran, especially the fearless young Iranian women. You are my heroes 💚🤍❤️ ⁣
⁣
⁣
#womenlifefreedom #mahsaamini #melodydancefit #nationaldanceday

Dance has & always will be my favorite method for stepping into my body & escaping my own intrusive thoughts. You don’t have to dance well nor do you need to dance fast—make it whatever you need it to be. This is about getting present and letting yourself release through the body. Studies show even moderate movement can have a positive impact on the nervous system. Having an embodiment practice will help you create awareness in your body. The first week of our @_dance_to_heal program goes in depth about body awareness and creating a line of communication from your mind to your body and vice verse. #dance #somatichealing #dancetoheal #healing #nervoussystem #melodydancefit

PRIORITIZING PLAY: It’s not just for the kids! It’s essential for adults as it unlocks tension and sparks creativity. Our society puts such an emphasis on work & productivity that we rarely value the importance of unstructured play. Play teaches us powerful lessons as it develops our resilience & eases our anxiety. Playing regularly will change the way you approach your entire life. It activates energy within, and simply put, makes us feel good! & we all know that when we feel good, we heal good 💪🏽⁣
⁣
Learn more about how to actually integrate play into adulthood in our online @_dance_to_heal program & if you’re in ATX come play with us 3 times a week in class! ⁣
⁣

It’s time to stop trying so hard and surrender to the present moment. I’ve been speaking & teaching about the healing power of dance for almost a decade now and I STILL feel the magic it works on myself and others. The reason dance is transformative is because it forces you to surrender to the present moment—the truth of where you are. You don’t have to be good at it, you don’t have to try hard at it, you just have to be willing to LET GO @_dance_to_heal program is opening very soon and I can’t wait to teach more people about the powerful tool of dance 🤩 DM me your email if you want to be first on our waitlist!! #somatichealing #melodydancefit #heal #dance #somatictherapy #dancefitness #healing

DANCING THRU DUALITY: Can you hold space for both the light & darkness inside of you? Can you embrace the discomfort and move through it? Are you disciplined enough to let go of trying to be perfect? Dance is my number one tool and my greatest teacher. It taps into something beyond the physical, it’s almost inexplicable—but I will spend my life trying to articulate the power it holds and the barriers it breaks. We talk about this duality & more in our @_dance_to_heal program —enrollment opens again soon 💫 in the meantime if you’re in ATX come dance with me Tuesdays 12PM Thursdays 6:45 Sundays 11AM www.melodydancefit.com #somatichealing #healing #dance #dancefitness #dancetoheal #melodydancefit

On my way home from this trip I was thinking about darkness (Cue Barbie quote “Do y’all ever think abt dying?”) We all have darkness within us and within our lives. And even though this seems to be a universal human experience, we’re all still a little ashamed of that darkness. We don’t always want to acknowledge it, so we avoid, repress, or shove a nice “but it could be SO much worse” to soften it up. We often associate darkness as negativity. But I’ve come to learn that my own darkness is directly correlated to my light and my power. My ability to empower people is a direct descendant of how completely disempowered I’ve felt in my life. My ability to make people feel seen and heard comes from me knowing how it feels to be invisible at times. Your darkness is often why you shine so incredibly bright to others. Is it a bummer sometimes? Sure. It absolutely can be. But there’s purpose behind it and there’s wisdom in it. It’s time for us to be a little less afraid of the dark, because it’s exactly how we’ve learned to step into the light. Sending love to everyone on a week that can be extremely light for some and depressingly heavy for others. ❤️ ❤️❤️
Thankful for my future hubby 💖

To be honest, I didn’t pick this career, it picked me. Once I taught my first dance fitness class I knew I had to find a way to make it my full time job. I’m called to this role because I’ve seen with my own eyes the rapid transformation & liberation dance gives humans. It’s exactly why I will never give up, stop, or get into another career. I know that dance is so much more than just a fun time. It saves people from depression, it helps cope with grief, and allows us to process things through our body that go beyond talk therapy. But you can’t just dance once. You have to do it as a ritual, and often. In our @_dance_to_heal we have you dance 3 times a week to allow for that cathartic release to kick in. #dancetoheal #melodydancefit

Be honest, how many times have you said “𝘐 𝘫𝘶𝘴𝘵 𝘥𝘪𝘥𝘯’𝘵 𝘭𝘪𝘬𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘪𝘳 𝘦𝘯𝘦𝘳𝘨𝘺.”?⁣
⁣
And how many times did you say with excitement “𝘖𝘔𝘎 𝘐 𝘭𝘰𝘷𝘦 𝘵𝘩𝘦𝘪𝘳 𝘦𝘯𝘦𝘳𝘨𝘺, 𝘪𝘵’𝘴 𝘦𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘺𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘯𝘨!”? ⁣
​⁣
If burnout has settled in your body you are likely saying “𝘐 𝘫𝘶𝘴𝘵 𝘩𝘢𝘷𝘦 𝘯𝘰 𝘦𝘯𝘦𝘳𝘨𝘺 𝘰𝘳 𝘥𝘦𝘴𝘪𝘳𝘦 𝘵𝘰 𝘥𝘰 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘵.”⁣
⁣
Even Beyonce and Drake have songs entitled “Energy” because the conversation around the currency of energy is SO pertinent.⁣
⁣
𝗘𝗻𝗲𝗿𝗴𝘆 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝗻𝗴𝗲𝘀 𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗿𝘆𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴.⁣
⁣
It isn’t about masking the negative energy or denying the low energy you have. It is about identifying tools that ground your energy & allow you to get to the root of YOU.⁣
⁣
Because energy is fluid and always on the go, it gets increasingly difficult to keep track of it.⁣
⁣
When we pour a little more energy into softening the relationship we have with our own mind, our own body, our own life, big changes happen. Taking small steps to invest in the things that make you feel alive will result in rapid & robust changes in your energy.⁣
​⁣
⁣
The truth about HOW to do this is more mundane than people expect. It’s in the rituals we commit to. The biggest problem? We don’t always know what fulfills us with the most energy. ⁣
​⁣
⁣
The first step is to observe your life and take notice. Scan your habits, your interactions, your routine and your level of energy after each.⁣
⁣
For Kristi, it was her relationship with her teaching job that left her incredibly burnt out. She had no energy left. Once she joined Dance To Heal, she realized she didn’t at all prioritize play into her life as a working adult. She spent her workday giving to her students only to come home and work on more to-do lists and tasks for her life.⁣
⁣
This was robbing her energy without even realizing it.⁣
⁣
She committed to the small change of dancing 3 times a week and leaning into the grounding tool of dance to play, laugh, and move without structure.⁣
⁣
The result? Her zestful energy came back FAST.⁣
⁣
So ask yourself this question,⁣
⁣
What’s one ritual you can lean into in 2024 that GIVES you energy?⁣
⁣
Comment your answer below!⁣
⁣
xoxo⁣
⁣
Melody
